                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14569098" author="philipthompson" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 13:33:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can confirm this is happening on 2.0.15. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blerer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blerer&quot;&gt;blerer&lt;/a&gt;, should this be possible? If not, then it&apos;s just the error message that&apos;s wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569144" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 14:19:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is valid. &lt;br/&gt;
Our test is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((cfm.getCfDef().isCompact || !cfm.getCfDef().isComposite) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cd.type != ColumnDefinition.Type.REGULAR)
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InvalidRequestException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Secondary indexes are not supported on PRIMARY KEY columns in COMPACT STORAGE tables&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that the type of the c column is &lt;tt&gt;ColumnDefinition.Type.COMPACT_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt; and not &lt;tt&gt;ColumnDefinition.Type.REGULAR&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569146" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 14:21:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue is valid. &lt;br/&gt;
Our test is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((cfm.getCfDef().isCompact || !cfm.getCfDef().isComposite) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cd.type != ColumnDefinition.Type.REGULAR)
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; InvalidRequestException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Secondary indexes are not supported on PRIMARY KEY columns in COMPACT STORAGE tables&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that the type of the c column is &lt;tt&gt;ColumnDefinition.Type.COMPACT_VALUE&lt;/tt&gt; and not &lt;tt&gt;ColumnDefinition.Type.REGULAR&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569314" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 15:51:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I was wrong.&lt;br/&gt;
We support secondary indices only on the compact tables that does not have clustering columns.&lt;br/&gt;
Which means that we should change the error message for this specific case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569641" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 19:52:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch make sure that we log a different error message for this specific case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14569645" author="blerer" created="Tue, 2 Jun 2015 19:53:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thobbs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thobbs&quot;&gt;thobbs&lt;/a&gt; can you review?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14598356" author="thobbs" created="Tue, 23 Jun 2015 20:58:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch looks good, but can you add some unit tests around this and push a branch so that cassci runs the full test suite?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
